-- Bank Negara, Berau Coal Energy, Vale: Indonesian Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-03-28T01:48:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-28/bank-negara-berau-coal-energy-vale-indonesian-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.2 percent to 4,079.38.  Nickel producers: Nickel for three-month delivery dropped 2
percent to $17,780 a metric ton in London yesterday, the lowest
close since Dec. 14.  PT Vale Indonesia (INCO)  , the nation’s
biggest producer of the metal, rose 2.3 percent to 3,375 rupiah
and  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM)  , the second-largest, advanced 1.7
percent to 1,800 rupiah.  PT Bank Negara Indonesia (BBNI)  : Indonesia’s third-
biggest state-owned bank plans to sell as much as $1 billion of
dollar bonds, corporate secretary Tribuana Tunggadewi said. The
lender hired Credit Suisse Group AG, Deutsche Bank AG and Morgan
Stanley as arrangers, she said.  Bank Negara  climbed 0.6 percent
to 3,975 rupiah.  PT Berau Coal Energy (BRAU)  : The coal producer’s 2011
net income surged to $133.9 million from $49.7 million a year
earlier, it said in a statement. Revenue increased to $1.66
billion from $1.06 billion, it said. Berau fell 1.9 percent to
510 rupiah.  PT BW Plantation (BWPT)  : The palm-oil producer plans to
add as much as 30,000 hectares of land this year as it seeks to
increase its reserves to 150,000 hectares by 2014 or 2015,
Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing Corporate Secretary
Kelik Irwantono. BW Plantation rose 1.9 percent to 1,630 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
